1 than Eighty Thousand Dollars ($80,000.00) per year, a twenty-percent
2 (20%) wage increase over the base amount the employee earned during
3 the 2024-2025 school year if the support employee is employed by the
4 same school district for the 2025-2026 school year. The dollar
5 amount of the salary increase required by this subsection shall be
6 prorated based upon the number of total hours of work performed by a
7 full-time-equivalent support employee. If a support employee is a
8 new employee of the school district, his or her starting salary
9 shall be a twenty-percent (20%) increase from the starting salary
10 for the same position during the 2024-2025 school year.
11 B. For the 2018-19 school year, each school district shall
12 provide to every support employee a wage increase over the base
13 amount the employee earned during the 2017-18 school year if the
14 support employee is employed by the same school district for the
15 2018-19 school year in the amount of One Thousand Two Hundred Fifty
16 Dollars ($1,250.00). The dollar amount of salary increase
17 authorized by this subsection shall be prorated based upon the
18 number of total hours of work performed by a full-time-equivalent
19 support employee.
20 B. C. The increase increases prescribed by this section shall be
21 in addition to any other compensation, increase in compensation, and
22 fringe benefits provided by the district or state, or mandated by
23 law or collective bargaining agreement, unless the hours or duties
24 of the support employee are reduced proportionately.
